Title: Hello World (Java Edition)
Short Description:
    A simple Java program that displays "Hello, World!" to the console.

Goal:
    Output a greeting message to demonstrate basic Java syntax.

========================================
üéÆ BLOCK 2 ‚Äî PROGRAM BEHAVIOR
========================================
On Start:
    - Java runtime locates the main method.
    - Execution begins at the main entry point.

On Execute:
    - System.out.println() sends OUTPUT_MESSAGE to the console.
    - Message appears in the terminal/console window.
    - Program exits with status 0.

========================================
üñçÔ∏è BLOCK 3 ‚Äî TUNING KNOBS
========================================
# These values are SAFE for humans to tweak.

OUTPUT_MESSAGE:         "Hello, World!"     # The message to display
CLASS_NAME:             HelloWorld          # Should match filename

========================================
üåê BLOCK 4 ‚Äî PUBLIC TEXT
========================================
CONSOLE_OUTPUT:         "Hello, World!"

========================================
üìù BLOCK 5 ‚Äî HUMAN NOTES
========================================
- Implementation notes:
    - Filename should be HelloWorld.java (matches class name).
    - Compile with: javac HelloWorld.java
    - Run with: java HelloWorld

- Code structure:
    public class HelloWorld {
        public static void main(String[] args) {
            System.out.println("Hello, World!");
        }
    }

- Future ideas:
    - Add user input.
    - Support multiple languages.
    - Colorized console output.
